The observed values for total proteins showed a tendency to peak on the 100th d.i. for group A and on the 72nd d.i. for group B. However, when compared to the control group this was not significant (p
 ≥ 0.05) (Fig. 1
).

The averages of the CK-MB isoenzyme presented an increase for infected dogs from the 30th d.i. with peaks on the 60th d.i. for group B and on the 90th and 150th d.i., for group A. A significant difference was observed when comparing the infected groups to the control group from the 30th to the 120th d.i. (p
 ≤ 0.05) (Fig. 3
).
